Configure DHCP Client:
On a Windows Client Machine:
Open the "Network and Sharing Center."
Click on "Change adapter settings."
Right-click on your network adapter and select "Properties."
Select "Internet Protocol Version 4 (TCP/IPv4)" and click "Properties."
Choose "Obtain an IP address automatically" and "Obtain DNS server address automatically."
Click "OK" to save the changes.
Test DHCP and DNS:
Renew IP Address:

Open Command Prompt on a client machine.
Run the following command to renew the IP address from the DHCP server:
powershell
Copy code
ipconfig /renew
Verify DNS Resolution:

Run the following command to check if DNS resolution is working:
powershell
Copy code
nslookup micha.com
Verify DHCP Lease:

Run the following command to check DHCP lease information:
powershell
Copy code
ipconfig /all
Ensure that the client receives a valid IP address from the DHCP server and can resolve DNS names.
